President Biden has authorized additional disaster assistance for the state of Arkansas in response to severe storms and tornadoes that occurred on March 31, 2023. The federal funding for emergency work, including debris removal and emergency protective measures, has been increased to 100 percent of the total eligible costs for a continuous 30-day period within the first 120 days of the incident. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.